    <text id="A6238T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Lorenzo Sibert telegrams David Evans from New York to announce success in an
                    endeavor.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>Blank No. 1.<lb/>THE WESTERN UNION TELEGRAPH COMPANY.<lb/> The rules of this
                    Company require that all messages received for transmission, shall be written on
                    the message blanks of the Company, under and subject to the conditions printed
                    thereon, which conditions have been agreed to by the sender of the following
                    message.<lb/>O. H. PALMER, Sec'y. WILLIAM ORTON, Pres't. <name type="recipient"/>
                    <name type="place">Dated New York</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-07">Nov 7th 1868</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>To David Evans</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Have met with perfect Success. Am well</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>Lorenzo Sibert</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Paid</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
